  "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"sjors\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"1766\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/user_avatar/delvingbitcoin.org/sjors/48/59_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> sjors:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It could be modernised to make use of ephemeral (dust) anchors (see <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/dbb9617e5f2c3e99d2d07f0b82dbb4ad861ad06e/bip-0431.mediawiki\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">BIP 341</a>), and to use taproot script paths rather than <code>OP_IF</code>.</p>\n<p>But for any vault construction to be useful in wallets, it needs to either fit in the existing <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/dbb9617e5f2c3e99d2d07f0b82dbb4ad861ad06e/bip-0380.mediawiki\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">BIP 380</a> output descriptor paradigm or develop an alternative.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://min.sc/v0.3/#github=examples/ctv-vault.minsc\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://min.sc/v0.3/#github=examples/ctv-vault.minsc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">min.sc</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    \n\n<h3><a href=\"https://min.sc/v0.3/#github=examples/ctv-vault.minsc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Minsc</a></h3>\n\n  <p>A mini scripting language for all things Bitcoin</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Cc: <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/shesek\">@shesek</a></p>",
